text: is the second daughter of the Crown Prince and Crown Princess of Japan and a member of the Japanese imperial family. She is a niece of Emperor Naruhito and the second-eldest grandchild of Emperor Emeritus Akihito and Empress Emerita Michiko. ==Biography== Princess Kako was born on 29 December 1994 at Imperial Household Agency Hospital in Tokyo Imperial Palace, Chiyoda, Tokyo. In April 2001, Princess Kako began Gakushuin Primary School and graduated in March 2007. Princess Kako entered Gakushuin Girls' Senior High School Tokyo in April 2007 and graduated in March 2013. She has an older sister, Mako Komuro, and a younger brother, Prince Hisahito. ==Titles and styles and Honors == 29 December 1994 Her Imperial Highness Princess Kako of Akishino National Honors -Grand Cordon of the Order of the Precious Crown (29 December 2014) ==References== ==Other websites== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:International Christian University alumni Category:Japanese princes and princesses Category:People from Tokyo
